worthy of Love to me. I have ob&s;erved,</HI>
&s;aid he, interrupting her, <HI>that he loves you,
and that he is very fond of telling you &s;o; nay
there appears a certain langui&s;hment in his Eyes,
when he is with you, which is not ob&s;ervable
in him, in the Company of other Ladies. I have
my &s;elf taken notice of that,</HI> added <HI>Emilia; I
