that the Dutche&s;s, with &s;ome other Ladies,
were to go to <HI>Wind&s;or.</HI> Thither he went al|&s;o,
with a re&s;olution of reproaching her
with the inju&s;tice he thought he had recei|ved
at her hands. But how great is the
